          <h3>Analysis of the WHO COVID-19 Pandemic</h3>
          <p>The objective of this project is to develop and implement a comprehensive public health strategy that leverages data-driven insights from the COVID-19 pandemic to enhance response measures, 
            improve healthcare access and mitigate the impact of future outbreaks globally. <br />
                                           
        <p>Key Insights: <br>
          ✪ Total Countries Affected: The pandemic has spread to 240 countries globally. <br>
          ✪ Cumulative Cases and Deaths: Globally, there have been 87bn cumulative COVID-19 cases and 1bn cumulative deaths. <br>
          ✪ Regional Trends: Europe, America, and Western Pacific regions have reported the highest new cases in the last 7 days.
         <br>
          ✪ Country-Specific Trends: The United States, India, Brazil, and France have reported the highest cumulative COVID-19 cases.
        </p>

          <p>Recommendations: <br>
          ✪ Continue to monitor the situation closely, particularly in the regions and countries with the highest case and death burdens. <br>
          ✪ Strengthen public health measures, such as testing, contact tracing, and vaccination campaigns, to control the spread of the virus. <br>
          ✪ Invest in research and development to better understand the evolving nature of the virus and develop more effective treatments and preventive strategies.<br>
          ✪ Prepare for potential future waves or variants of the virus by maintaining a robust and adaptable pandemic response framework.<br>
          ✪ Enhance international cooperation and coordination to ensure equitable access to medical resources and support countries with limited healthcare capacities.</p>
